history.content:
I enrolled in 12 units  in phase 1. I also set up a delayed swap in phase 1 as well.  This means that in phase 1 i was enrolled in 12 units and waitlisted in 4 units. I know that swaps allow you to go past the unit limits of that phase. However during phase 1, when I tried enrolling into a class after setting up the swap, it did not allow me to enroll because it would go over the unit limit. I was able to enroll into the class first and then set up the swap for some reason.

I want to enroll into a breadth phase 2. In phase 2 will I not be able to enroll into the breadth because it would supposedly "go over the unit limit for phase 2" even though the waitlist swap units should not count towards the unit limit for phase 2? Do I have no choice but to cancel the delayed swap, add the breadth, and then set up the delated swap again? Please advise. I would like to be able to keep the waitlist position that I have currently and not have to be at the back of the waitlist because of cancelling and then adding the delayed swap again.
history.subject: Urgent Course Enrollment Phase 2 Question
